Service management ensures that cloud services consistently meet agreed business expectations.

Key service management activities include:

* Service request fulfillment
* Incident management
* Problem management
* Change management
* Service reporting
* Continuous improvement

For example, an IT support team processes user requests for additional Azure resources while following approval workflows and maintaining service quality.

A real-life use case is enterprises adopting IT service management practices to improve customer satisfaction and operational consistency.

Effective service management aligns technology services with business objectives.
